    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Netlify is broken because of sass, it works again now\r\n\r\n@vvo @Haroenv \r\nif you encounter this error on another project, it's because the version used by default by yarn is old and has a bug with post install of npm packages. To solve this you need to specify the version of Yarn using a environment variable on netlify: YARN_VERSION",
    "created_at": "2017-09-04T16:22:13Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2305#issuecomment-326997449",
